# RDF Changelog

## 3.0.7

### Context-Efficient Reads (AST primitives + audit wiring)

[New] canonical/commands/r-util-code-map.md: structural map of source files with per-symbol line ranges; language dispatch covering Python (ast), shell (awk), TypeScript/JavaScript (ctags/grep), Go, Rust, C/C++ (ctags), Ruby, with tree-sitter preferred when present; configurable threshold via governance/conventions.md (code-map-threshold, default 500); symbol-filter mode; uniform output shape so downstream skills can parse it
[Change] canonical/commands/r-audit.md Stage 1c: baseline pattern scan via /r-util-code-scan all; report written to .rdf/work-output/audit-baseline-patterns.md and threaded to Stage 2a subagent as extra context — UNTRACKED hits promoted to formal findings, TRACKED hits passthrough
[Change] canonical/commands/r-audit.md Stage 2a: reviewer dispatch gains large-file discipline directive — /r-util-code-map before reading any source file over 500 lines
[Change] canonical/commands/r-audit.md --quick mode: replaces ad-hoc anti-pattern grep with canonical /r-util-code-scan all call; baseline output folded directly into lightweight AUDIT.md
[New] canonical/commands/r-refresh.md Stage 1d: anti-pattern drift delta via /r-util-code-scan all counts-only output; snapshot at .rdf/governance/.scan-baseline.json; skipped for state/github scopes; first-run behavior creates baseline without delta
[Change] canonical/commands/r-refresh.md Stage 6c: Drift Detection block now carries one-line anti-pattern drift summary (sign-prefixed deltas per changed class); no per-file findings table in refresh output — users directed to /r-util-code-scan <class> for detail
[Change] README.md: utility command count 14 → 15; added /r-util-code-map row; totals updated (34 → 35 commands)
[Change] RDF.md: command counts (34 → 35, 14 utility → 15 utility); VERSION reference (3.0.6 → 3.0.7)
[Change] VERSION: 3.0.7

## 3.0.6

### Harness Primitives (5-item release)

[New] canonical/commands/r-verify-claim.md: slash command for evidence verification; 5 closed-set claim classes (commit-landed, pattern-absent, pattern-present, file-unchanged, behavior-observable); UNVERIFIABLE verdict for unclassifiable claims; produces evidence lines suitable for engineer result files
[New] canonical/reference/framework.md: EVIDENCE block in engineer result schema — one line per phase claim; citation forms <path>:<line>, <cmd> → <output>, <sha> <message>; required for STATUS: DONE; arrow accepted as → or ->
[Change] canonical/agents/engineer.md §Evidence: structured TDD_EVIDENCE + EVIDENCE two-section description replacing narrative list
[New] canonical/agents/dispatcher.md Gate 1: structural EVIDENCE check — empty or missing block on DONE produces NEEDS_CONTEXT verdict
[Change] canonical/agents/dispatcher.md §Load: parse Regression-case from target phase and pass to engineer; pass phase N to QA for result file path derivation
[New] canonical/agents/qa.md §Protocol: EVIDENCE re-validation step (scope-gated) — derive result file from .rdf/work-output/phase-<N>-result.md; re-run commands and compare output; scope {docs,focused} records SKIPPED
[New] canonical/agents/qa.md report format: EVIDENCE row in ### Checks table with PASS/FAIL/SKIPPED outcomes
[Change] canonical/agents/reviewer.md §Challenge Mode: Verification protocol subsection — require /r-verify-claim on MUST-FIX assertions about current state; exempt design opinions and SHOULD-FIX findings
[New] canonical/commands/r-plan.md preamble template: **Plan Version:** 3.0.6 marker for version-aware schema validation
[New] canonical/commands/r-plan.md phase template: **Regression-case** field — named test reference OR N/A with closed-set category (docs/performance/logging/refactor/security); security category requires CVE/bug/issue reference
[Change] canonical/commands/r-plan.md mandatory fields: add Regression-case to Mode/Accept/Test/Edge cases set
[New] canonical/commands/r-plan.md quality checklist: checks #9 (Regression-case) and #10 (Plan Version); Plan Quality Standard items #14, #15
[New] canonical/commands/r-build.md minimum schema validation: include Regression-case; reject unknown category; reject security N/A without CVE/bug/issue reference; skip validation on pre-3.0.6 plans (no Plan Version preamble marker)
[New] profiles/core/reference/ignore-defaults.md: seed content for .rdf/governance/ignore.md with conservative defaults (node_modules, vendor, dist, build, target, __pycache__, .venv, venv, *.pyc, .rdf/work-output/, docs/specs/)
[New] canonical/commands/r-init.md §Generate: ignore.md: first-time generation from defaults with user-modified-merge behavior
[Change] canonical/commands/r-refresh.md Stage 3b: add ignore.md row; create on pre-3.0.6 consumer projects; append missing defaults under "# Added by /r-refresh" heading
[Remove] adapters/agents-md/adapter.sh: _amd_extract_governance_section (broken — produced "(governance file not found)" on every invocation)
[New] adapters/agents-md/adapter.sh: _amd_extract_canonical_section (heading-based extraction from canonical/reference/framework.md or CLAUDE.md.ref; visible "section not found" marker on rename)
[Change] adapters/agents-md/sections.json: replace governance sources with canonical sources; new sections (Operating Primitives, Architecture Overview, Result File Artifacts, Commands); max_lines 150 → 200
[Change] adapters/agents-md/output/AGENTS.md: regenerated from new sources — 60+ lines, zero "(governance file not found)" strings
[New] tests/adapter.bats: +8 @test cases covering r-verify-claim file existence, engineer EVIDENCE declaration, dispatcher Gate 1 references, r-plan Regression-case field, r-build schema validation, ignore-defaults structural check (Goal 4), agents-md clean output, rdf doctor zero FAILs after generate (Goal 8)
[Change] VERSION, RDF.md, README.md: bumped to 3.0.6; command count 33 → 34 in README.md

## 3.0.5

### CLAUDE.md.ref Integration
[Change] CLAUDE.md: reference CLAUDE.md.ref (operating primitives — Trust but Verify, Scope Discipline, Adversarial Review, Context Preservation, Comment Discipline, Safe Execution); file was added via GitHub UI on 2026-04-17 but never wired into the workflow; this commit takes local ownership going forward and makes it discoverable from the project's top-level CLAUDE.md

### Docs Quality Overhaul
[Change] README.md: restructured to numbered sections (## 1-11), new `## 3. Configuration` section covering environment variables + per-project setup + convention inheritance chain, new `## 4. Usage` section consolidating Command Reference + CLI Reference + exit codes table, new `## License` section; updated counts from 31 commands / 10 scripts to 33 / 12; added 2 new scripts to table (comment-metrics.sh, comment-snapshot.sh); updated utility commands list to include /r-audit-slop and /r-context-audit; updated directory tree to show state/ helpers (rdf-state.sh, context-audit.sh, rotate-work-output.sh); updated doctor scope count to 7 checks (added content-drift)
[Change] lib/cmd/doctor.sh: relax README section checks to accept optional `## N. ` numbered prefix on Quick Start / Configuration / Usage — consistent with the same file's numbered-sections requirement; prior regex required literal `## Quick Start` which conflicted with numbered-section convention
[Change] CLAUDE.md: added one-paragraph parent-CLAUDE.md reference at top — satisfies `rdf doctor` drift check and documents inheritance explicitly
[Change] VERSION + RDF.md: bumped to 3.0.5 to match CHANGELOG section header

### Context Audit Command
[New] canonical/commands/r-context-audit.md: command driver for `state/context-audit.sh` (committed in Phase 3) — runs the measurement script, parses JSON, renders a scored report (0-100 CLEAN/NEEDS_WORK/BLOATED/CRITICAL) with boot-cost breakdown, rdf-state.sh field analysis, work-output accumulation, session history totals, and prioritized 3-tier fix recommendations; supports `--fix` for Tier 1 auto-remediation and `--save-baseline` for drift tracking via `~/.rdf/context-audit-baseline.json`

### BATS Adapter Test Suite
[New] tests/adapter.bats: hermetic BATS test suite for the claude-code adapter round-trip; 7 tests covering: expected file tree generation, canonical body preservation in deployed output, .rdf-hash sidecar emission (Phase 7 regression), idempotency on second generate run, and drift detection (corrupted deployed file causes doctor content-drift FAIL with file cited)
[New] tests/Makefile: minimal make test target; system bats (no batsman submodule); documents install instructions for apt and brew
[New] tests/README.md: explains BATS strategy decision (system bats over batsman submodule), test coverage summary, hermeticity contract
[New] tests/fixtures/canonical/commands/r-example.md: minimal frontmatter-free command fixture with RDF_TEST_MARKER_r_example for grep assertions
[New] tests/fixtures/canonical/agents/example.md: minimal frontmatter-free agent fixture with RDF_TEST_MARKER_example_agent for grep assertions

### GitHub Actions CI Workflow
[New] .github/workflows/ci.yml: minimal CI workflow on push/PR to main; lint job runs bash -n syntax check and shellcheck -S error on all source shell files (bin/, lib/, state/, adapters/*/*.sh, canonical/scripts/); doctor job runs rdf generate claude-code then rdf doctor --scope content-drift to verify adapter health; tests job conditional on tests/Makefile (stub for Phase 10 BATS suite)

### Progress Tracking Reference
[New] canonical/reference/progress-tracking.md: canonical superset of the Progress Tracking protocol — CRITICAL batch-creation rule, TaskCreate branch with activeForm example, in_progress/completed guidance, >30s spinner note, N/A phase handling, checkbox fallback for Gemini CLI/Codex
[Change] canonical/commands/r-init.md: replace 36-line inline Progress Tracking block with reference link + compact task-name list for /r-init's 5 phases
[Change] canonical/commands/r-start.md: replace 12-line inline Progress Tracking block with reference link + single-task spec (Initialize session) and fallback note
[Change] canonical/commands/r-save.md: replace 35-line inline Progress Tracking block with reference link + compact task-name list for /r-save's 6 phases

### Doctor Content-Drift Detection
[New] adapters/claude-code/adapter.sh: emit .rdf-hash sidecar next to each deployed agent and command file during 'rdf generate claude-code'; sidecar contains SHA-256 of canonical source body (pre-frontmatter); sha1sum fallback if sha256sum absent
[New] lib/cmd/doctor.sh: add content-drift check scope; hashes deployed file body (YAML frontmatter stripped for agents) and compares to .rdf-hash sidecar; FAIL with specific file name on mismatch; WARN on missing sidecar (directs user to regenerate); usable as --scope content-drift or as part of full 'rdf doctor' run

### Release Packaging
[New] .gitattributes: export-ignore rules for docs/, assets/, tests/, .github/, .rdf/, .claude/, .pytest_cache/, and working files (CLAUDE.md, PLAN.md, MEMORY.md, AUDIT.md) — prevents dev-only artifacts from shipping in git archive / GitHub release tarballs

### Stale Artifact Cleanup
[Remove] .pytest_cache/: deleted from RDF repo root — RDF has no Python tests; stale artifact from an aborted path
[Remove] advanced-policy-firewall: full-branch-diff.patch (521 KB, 34 days old) deleted from .rdf/work-output/
[Remove] s3perf: PLAN-tier0-909cbaa-239722c.md (60 KB) deleted from .rdf/memory/ — misfiled plan
[Change] Run live rotation via rotate-work-output.sh against 4 projects (LMD: 227 pruned, BFD: 175, Sigforge: 150, APF: 119)
[Change] session-safety.md and docs/superpowers/: SKIPPED — both have active references in docs/; preserved per governance (grep evidence in phase report)

### Work-Output Rotation
[New] state/rotate-work-output.sh: age-based pruning of *.md result files (default 14-day mtime threshold) with PLAN.md cross-reference guard to preserve active phase files; size-based truncation of agent-feed.log to last 1000 lines when file exceeds 100 KB; --dry-run, --age, and --size-cap flags
[Change] rdf generate claude-code: deploys rotate-work-output.sh to ~/.rdf/state/ alongside rdf-state.sh and context-audit.sh

### Context Audit Timeout Guards
[New] context-audit.sh: add TIMEOUT_PREFIX ("timeout 30") — same pattern as rdf-state.sh — wrapping the git log call in the per-repo recency sort and both python3 invocations (field breakdown + baseline comparison)
[New] context-audit.sh: extract _count_md_files() helper replacing 8 near-duplicate find+wc patterns across skills, agents, memory, and work-output sections
[Fix] context-audit.sh: replace per-file stat loop over JSONL session files with find -printf byte sum; reduces Section 8 from ~15s to <0.1s on machines with thousands of JSONL files

### Hang Prevention
[Fix] rdf-state.sh: wrap all 14 git invocations with TIMEOUT_PREFIX variable ("timeout 30") to prevent indefinite stalls on locked repos, orphaned tracking branches, or slow remotes; TIMEOUT_PREFIX is empty on systems without the timeout binary (CentOS 6 minimal) for zero-regression fallback

### Session Startup Fix
[Fix] r-start: replace broken relative-path + undefined RDF_HOME + implicit find fallback with explicit probe order: ~/.rdf/state/rdf-state.sh → /root/admin/work/proj/rdf/state/rdf-state.sh → inline git fallback
[New] rdf generate claude-code: deploy rdf-state.sh and context-audit.sh to ~/.rdf/state/ with executable bit; creates directory if absent

### New Commands
[New] /r-audit-slop — AI slop audit (dead code, orphan helpers, noop functions, tautological guards, redundant implementations, over-engineered abstractions). Promoted from /r-util-slop-scan with two additional verification passes: independent sentinel peer-review of HIGH findings and engineer FP-validation pass (read-only). --quick flag restores single-agent behavior. Discovery-first protocol: Phase 0 builds a per-project call-site manifest before scanning, preventing the false-positive wall that hits naive dead-code scanners. Confidence gated on attached grep evidence; density safeguard triggers re-scan when >10 HIGH findings in a category.
[Remove] /r-util-slop-scan — superseded by /r-audit-slop (use --quick for equivalent single-agent behavior)

### Model Cost Optimization
[New] Dispatcher: scope-based model routing for engineer dispatch (sonnet for docs/focused, opus for multi-file+)
[New] Dispatcher: reviewer model routing documentation (sentinel stays opus, challenge dispatches on sonnet)
[Change] r-review: challenge mode dispatches reviewer on sonnet via model override
[Change] r-spec: challenge review dispatches reviewer on sonnet via model override
[Change] r-plan: challenge review dispatches reviewer on sonnet via model override
[Change] Default session model: claude-sonnet-4-6 (settings.json)

